<subSubSection id="2FF58DC7BA5995EAD22CC1B4D411D3E6" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="60EFE0AEA386979142DAF46A0BDBA940" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="546F2A68E1D760F9901D782AC3CBA3F6" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName id="0CB03FCFF1BBAACC60BD20DB4773C263" authorityName="Firat" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cirsium semzinanicum" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semzinanicum">
<emphasis id="E829C0D8B6C3D57B07DF02619CB40DCD" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Cirsium semzinanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="DE66352F5E3A3C7E941EDA912570AD34" authorityName="Petr" authorityYear="1964" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cirsium karduchorum" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="karduchorum">
<emphasis id="8632F55BF6CEE6021DB8214E4C34CF69" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Cirsium karduchorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Petr. in its stems 100-150 cm tall (vs. 50-100 cm tall, robust), basal leaves 15-25 
<normalizedToken id="1D3F072399B1FE5774E5B6D8C150CF01" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
9-14 cm &quot;excluding 10-18 petiole&quot;, green, (vs. 30-40 
<normalizedToken id="3E81C5F82D56B11C3A8C907D3F827436" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
15-20 cm &quot;excluding 15-20 cm petiole&quot;, bluish-green), involucre 15-25 
<normalizedToken id="8F148B3389D35C7A9B3E7F3EF3041F38" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
20-30 mm ovoid tosubglobose (vs. 25-30 
<normalizedToken id="FCE3CC566DAD2CB2FEFFD6F1BE173511" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(30-)40-50 mm depressed subglobose tobroadly obovoid), phyllaries 9-12-seriate 
<normalizedToken id="ADA361AFFAF1EDAA58D1DC936A2416F0" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
erecto-refIexed (vs. 11-14-seriate refIexed or recurved), achen brownish 7-9 
<normalizedToken id="1DDFB40A5B5A074C2831082B50516867" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm (vs. bright grayish brown 6-7.5 
<normalizedToken id="ABA9EFD8507E1A0EEC0353749389D0FB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F53944B7CC24E175FA38C0B4FA00373B" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph id="76E9B2826F819DF5198844CAA06C647E" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E274F50A19AD157A72FAE8ED74ED8C31" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Perennial, few stemmed from base, erect, 100-150 cm tall, unwinged but longitudinally striate, glabrous-glaucous, with few branches above, sterile shoots at the base. Basal leaves long-petiolate, petioles 10-18 cm long, winged, with large auricules; lamina broadly elliptic in outline, 15-25 
<normalizedToken id="6034169EA333924A187C83AFBB3B7AE5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
9-14 cm, green, very sparsely spinulose-strigose above with 0.5-0.9 mm long, adpressed setae, ca 1-3 per 2 mm square, otherwise densely arachnoid; lower surface very sparsely arachnoid, 3/4 pinnatifid with 4-5-pairred, 5-8 
<normalizedToken id="B50CF517F372C69B2A778422B7360997" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-5 lateral and terminal lobes with stout 7-12 mm apical spine. Middle cauline leaves similar but smaller tobasal leaves, petioles 1-6 cm long. lamina broadly elliptic in outline 4-8 
<normalizedToken id="44A3F8C92CA2620CD1106EA98EE2BC86" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2,5-4 cm long, lateral and terminal lobes 3/4 pinnatifid with 3-5 lobes, spinulose-strigose above with 0.7-1.2 mm long, adpressed setae, ca 4-6 per 2 mm square, otherwise densely arachnoid with stout 6-9 mm apical spine. Upper cauline leaves similar middle cauline leaves but smaller and sessile. shortly auriculate. Uppermost (involucral) leaves 2-3, 1-3 cm long, linear-lanceolate with sinuate-dentate margin, shorter than involucre, sessile. Capitula erect, 1(-2) on each branch, compound corymbose with 15-30-capitula, 26-35 mm 
<normalizedToken id="DA18AF1DA0AD5C42AE8F63056022C7EA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-30 mm, sessile or peduncles 1-2 cm long; involucre 15-25 
<normalizedToken id="20792F44123F2AFB81F2F8D5BC8EAA77" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
20-30 mm, ovoid tosubglobose; phyllaries 9-12-seriate, adpressed, glabrous, greensh-yellowish, 
<normalizedToken id="45E9CF65C50F2966A2BCEB5BE5E16C3D" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
erecto-reflexed, the outer 8-10 
<normalizedToken id="43594CFE011D6B5098C39986E4C14039" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, with reflexed, ovate-oblong, 3-5 
<normalizedToken id="1DD6FF5854375325421717D8F73AF73F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.4 mm long apical spine; 
<pageBreakToken id="50A4181C21CCE4A63C9281C2362D50FC" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" start="start">the</pageBreakToken>
median 10-14 
<normalizedToken id="6287C27F433B4B286960DD225E9B104E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm long, with 
<normalizedToken id="52E208300AE4F381E731863B268FF767" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
reflexed, oblong-lanceolate, 4-6 
<normalizedToken id="B2BBE3888617EFF06936C81219973189" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.3 mm long apical spine; the inner 16-21 
<normalizedToken id="EE2CF38F4DFD414DC2396AD9B93FC965" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, linear-lanceolate, 5-7 
<normalizedToken id="5976C7D8AE67C02236661421BABE4DE4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-0.2 mm long apical spine. Corolla pinkish-whitish, 26-32 mm long. lobed to1/4-1/5. 
<pageBreakToken id="F62E1ACE072A9BE75E96D5F610A06914" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" start="start">Style</pageBreakToken>
15-19 mm long, exerted, shortly bilobed; filaments 5-7 mm long, densely hairy; Achenes brownish, 7-9 
<normalizedToken id="A168B9C5173BDEFC8F55B9193AD918A6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, oblong, asymmetric, slightly compressed. Pappus 16-18 mm long, plumose, dirty white, or light brown.
</paragraph>
