.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB4E7C656CE530E39A2291C28EBF6FF7" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Flowering and fruiting, from July to September.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="66C120260F4EE1DAE80D0B8BA3D645D5" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" type="vernacular name">
<paragraph id="95F616993E7E7008CF372E3B9BF6CF5C" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Vernacular name.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF5C239383D7773116858B302B38441B" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="71B66596D237595309EE2DA7679C6AC7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cirsium" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04F6023C09DB516B08DB29E2F89E72A0" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Cirsium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. are called as 
<normalizedToken id="7BD115AD6737707390356B528533394D" originalValue="“Kîvar”">&quot;Kivar&quot;</normalizedToken>
by the local people of the 
<normalizedToken id="26BAFC86B6A7DFCC78DF6F5046AD2A0E" originalValue="Hakkâri">Hakkari</normalizedToken>
province (
<bibRefCitation id="2D4E9DE434CF888AB0BB5345ABF68A8D" author="Firat, M" journalOrPublisher="Kalkan Ofset, Ankara" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="B8" refString="Firat, M, 2013. Ferhenga Naven Riweken Bi Kurdi / Kuertce Bitki Adlari Soezluegue/Dictionary of Plant Names in Kurdish. Kalkan Ofset, Ankara" title="Ferhenga Naven Riweken Bi Kurdi / Kuertce Bitki Adlari Soezluegue / Dictionary of Plant Names in Kurdish." year="2013">
<normalizedToken id="C61B026A330E4071E8A0E845ADCD5952" originalValue="Fırat">Firat</normalizedToken>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C2ADB92DD26BA3B3C3C0D16399F3BE6" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="EFE3CC373FA677D7983D128D411417C4" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="903D5EE2C7CFDE801951F8559A7CAC8E" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
The specific epithet is derived from the name of the 
<normalizedToken id="2FB11D4A1FD6CE9406DB293FAE8B9232" originalValue="Şemzinan">Semzinan</normalizedToken>
(
<normalizedToken id="9178CA66AC5108345A472905047EA8AD" originalValue="Şemdinli">Semdinli</normalizedToken>
) province where type material was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D8C6C450C29FC195F0AD337534E3322" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2ADE74090D704C4224B2C17C67744B2A" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Distribution and conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B5ED3E81512928CCE2A02B2EE9CAB1C" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="1593B07E136B7B90D20227156A0D42CF" authorityName="Firat" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cirsium semzinanicum" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semzinanicum">
<emphasis id="C2DA2EB3B14F200C0E006A999E1C598A" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Cirsium semzinanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<normalizedToken id="835ACB6892FCCC5903CB2FC18A1E581A" originalValue="Hakkâri">Hakkari</normalizedToken>
province in Turkey. The number of mature individuals is approximately 600 and is known from 3 locations (criteria B2ab [i.iii]). Therefore, it should be regarded as belonging tothe IUCN Vulnerable (VU) threat category (
<bibRefCitation id="B2A7989A7FDB05570BAFCBF9B3513953" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland, Switzerland" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="B10" refString="IUCN, 2014. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 11. IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland, Switzerland" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 11." year="2014">IUCN 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
